items.desc: Welcome to the Monopoly Wiki! This wiki is all about everything and anything related to the board game, Monopoly. We are hopefully just on the verge of becoming a comprehensive Monopoly Encyclopedia and need everyone's help! Here, feel free to edit or create a new page. Anything relating to Monopoly is allowed.

items.desc: Welcome... to Juras- wait, no, wrong line. Welcome... to Dinopedia! This is a wiki all about prehistoric life including, you guessed it, dinosaurs. If you want to share your knowledge and passion for the time when reptiles ruled the Earth, join us today. This is a community site that anyone can edit, including you!

items.name: Fanon Wiki
items.title: Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Hello, and welcome to the Fanon Wiki.
items.desc: This is a wiki about fan created characters, timelines, and anything else about existing storylines, you can create fanon relating to anything. You can create an article by typing the title in the box below and clicking "create article" and start typing in there. Welcome to our rich and growing community!

items.name: Halo Fanon
items.title: Halo Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to Halo Fanon
items.desc: Halo Fanon is a community wiki dedicated to writing high quality fiction pertaining to the Halo universe Over ten years old and with over 10,000 pages produced by a population of ambitious fan fiction writers, Halo Fanon contributors are encouraged to write stories and articles about the Halo-verse, collaborate with other users and get feedback from more experienced users. Halo Fanon is a place to show off writing ability - or learn to write better with a constructive and dedicated community, and to interact with a community of Halo fans that care about the franchise.

items.name: PokéFanon
items.title: PokéFanon
items.headline: Create your own Pokemon, regions, trainers, teams and story lines!
items.desc: The PokéFanon Encyclopedia is a non-canon encylcopedia that is not endorsed by Gamefreak, Nintendo or any other for-profit company (as of yet!), and can be used by anyone! This wiki features fan-made Pokémon, regions, games and stories. Our goal is for you to create all the Pokemon you can imagine!!

items.name: Fantendo - Nintendo Fanon Wiki
items.title: Fantendo - Nintendo Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Fantendo, the Nintendo Fanon Wiki
items.desc:
Fantendo is a community-based fanon Wiki. Though the wiki is based around Nintendo, we really accept fanon based around any type of video game! Come here to create and read about fan games, fan fiction, or even original fiction. In our community we discuss video gaming news and events as well.

Fantendo is a Wiki that was created in 2007. Our community has grown tremendously since then, with so many great additions to our userbase and our content. Our administration has grown as well; our administrators are supportive and humorous. 

Since 2007, we've grown to have almost 25,000 articles from enthusiastic Nintendo fans or other video game fans. It would be nice to have more great additions to our wiki from new users to the community! If you're going to join, don't be afraid to introduce yourself with a blogpost!

See and feel the excitement in the Fantendo Wiki!

items.name: Dino Crisis Wiki

items.desc: An encyclopedia on Capcom's Dino Crisis franchise.

items.name: Naruto Fanon Wiki
items.title: Naruto Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Naruto Fanon Wiki
items.desc: Naruto Fanon Wiki is undoubtedly dedicated to fanon/fanfiction about Naruto, the popular manga and anime series. In their own words, Naruto Fanon Wiki strives to become the preeminent and largest Naruto Fanon fanbase in the world and has over 25000 pages worth of content that readers of the series would enjoy.

items.name: The Sopranos Wiki
items.title: The Sopranos Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Sopranos Wiki!
items.desc: The Sopranos is an American television drama created by David Chase. The series revolves around the New Jersey-based Italian-American mobster Tony Soprano (James Gandolfini) and the difficulties he faces as he tries to balance the conflicting requirements of his home life and the criminal organization he heads. Those difficulties are often highlighted through his ongoing professional relationship with psychiatrist Jennifer Melfi (Lorraine Bracco). The show features Tony's family members and Mafia associates in prominent roles and story arcs, most notably his wife Carmela (Edie Falco) and his cousin and protégé Christopher Moltisanti (Michael Imperioli).

items.name: Harry Potter Fanon Wiki
items.title: Harry Potter Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Harry Potter Fanon Wiki!
items.desc: You have reached an encyclopedic resource and community gathering spot for all things related to the vast and diverse world of Harry Potter fan-fiction and fanon. As of now, we are the #1 Harry Potter fanon database anyone can edit.

items.name: Transformers Fanon Wiki
items.title: Transformers Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Transformers Fanon Wikia!
items.desc:
The Transformers Fanon Wikia, commonly called Transfanon, is a wikia for making up transformers characters, story lines, or anything else Transformers related. Everything here is non-canon! None of it is real! 

We allow users to make their own stories without them being deleted like they would be on the Transformers Wiki. They would only be deleted if they have offensive text or have no purpose and have little sense (Joke Articles are an exception).

Happy editing!

items.name: Doctor Who Fanon
items.title: Doctor Who Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to the Doctor Who Fanon Wikia!
items.desc: Doctor Who Fanon is Wikia's first & largest Doctor Who Fan Fiction site. Our goal is to provide a free online outlet that gives you the means to write your own adventures about the Doctor Who Universe. Since its establishment in 2007, Doctor Who Fanon has reached the size of over 2,000 articles. May your fictions be about The Doctor, those ruthless Daleks, or the nasty Cybermen, you can let your imagination take flight on our site!

items.name: Death Note Wiki
items.title: Death Note Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Death Note Wiki!
items.desc: Death Note Wiki is a community database about the Death Note series created by Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata. Death Note centers around a high school student named Light Yagami, who discovers a supernatural notebook that allows him to kill anyone simply by writing the victim's name while picturing his or her face. Disgusted with the amount of crime in the world, Light decides to use the notebook to eliminate criminals and become the "god" of a "New World," inhabited only by those that he deems "good." Now accompanying Light is a Shinigami (Death God) named Ryuk, who dropped the notebook to Earth from the Shinigami Realm. After a number of criminals suddenly die, talk on the internet leads to the deaths being attributed to a mysterious killer that is deemed "Kira" (the Japanese pronunciation of the English word "killer"). As the death toll quickly continues to rise, law enforcement agencies around the world begin to take notice and all are unable to find any reason for the deaths to have had occurred. Unbeknownst to Light, a Detective known only as "L" has also noticed the strange deaths and is already on Lights tail. After publicly voicing his intention to find Kira and bring him to justice, a cat and mouse game begins between Light and L as they both try to stay ahead of the other and uncover their opponents name.

items.name: The Elder Scrolls Fanon
items.title: The Elder Scrolls Fanon
items.headline: The Elder Scrolls Fanon Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to The Elder Scrolls Fanon Wikia! The Elder Scrolls Fanon Wikia is an Elder Scrolls wikia dedicated to fan fiction! The wikia hosts articles subject to fan fiction within the Elder Scrolls universe created by writers with their own sense of imagination. The site is not limited only to fan-fiction but modding and machinima! Enter now to learn more and how to contribute to the site!

items.name: Marvel Fanon
items.title: Marvel Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to Marvel Fanon Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to Marvel Fanon Wikia! The Marvel Fanon Wikia is a site for all fans of Marvel who also love writing fan fiction! Enter now to create your own story or to collaborate with other authors in writing an original Marvel fan fiction! Check out the Marvel Fanon Wikia and find out how you can contribute!

items.name: Burn Wiki
items.title: Burn Wiki
items.headline: BURN Notice Wiki
items.desc:
Burn Notice is a TV Series all about spies! It focuses on a spy, Michael Westen and his life after he receives his burn notice. 

What's a Burn Notice you ask?

It's an official document issued from one agency to other agencies stating that a source or asset is no longer reliable. This results in all of the individual's information to be disregarded or "BURNED".

Each episode focuses partly on Michael trying to figure why he received his 'burn notice' as well as dealing with clients who need his help. The awesome narration in each episode by Michael could give you tips in being a spy.

Burn Notice is a quality show with the edge and attitude to BURN.

Come check out our wiki and learn more about spies (like Michael) and spy knowledge/wisdom.

items.name: Slipknot Wiki
items.title: Slipknot Wiki
items.headline: The Wikia for fans of Slipknot
items.desc: Fellow Slipknot fans are free to join us at the Slipknot Wikia community where we pride ourselves on being a source of information in everything related to the band Slipknot as well as the various side-projects of the members. We have information about the Slipknot DVDS, discography, tour dates, downloads, and more.

items.name: Burnout Wiki
items.title: Burnout Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Burnopedia!
items.desc:
Burnopedia -the Burnout Wiki- is a wiki based on the Burnout Series operating since 2007. It has information on all of the aspects of the games, such as vehicles, locations, events, stunts and driving skills, songs, and many many more.

It has also become a friendly and active community with weekly in-game clan meetings and communal forums.

items.name: Anomaly Research Centre

items.desc: The Anomaly Research Centre is an ever-growing online encyclopedia dedicated to the British television series "Primeval" and its recent Canadian spin-off series "Primeval: New World".  The basic premise of the show is that fourth-dimensional rifts in space and time called Anomalies start opening and long extinct creatures from the past enter into the present.  A small team of people are sent to deal with the incursions.

items.title: FunOrb Wiki
items.headline: Check out the FunOrb Wiki!
items.desc: FunOrb is a website run by Jagex, dedicated to small, Java-based browser games. It earns money with a "freemium" model: most players play for free, and Jagex earns money by displaying advertising to them, and some pay a monthly subscription for various benefits. FunOrb was launched on 27 February 2008 in English and German with 18 games, a small number of which were updated versions or sequels of games from the original Jagex website.

items.name: No More Heroes Wiki
items.title: No More Heroes Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the No More Heroes Wikia!
items.desc:
No More Heroes Wikia is an English, web-based, free content encyclopedia project of all things regarding the No More Heroes Wii video game series, developed by Grasshopper Manufacture. No More Heroes Wiki is written collaboratively by volunteers from all around the world. Its articles can be edited by anyone with access to the Internet, simply by clicking the edit link at the top of the page. 

In every article, links will guide you to associated articles, often with additional information. Anyone is welcome to add further information, cross-references, or even citations, so long as they do so within No More Heroes Wiki's editing policies and to an appropriate standard. One need not fear accidentally damaging No More Heroes Wiki when adding or improving information, as other editors are always around to advise or correct obvious errors, if needed, and the No More Heroes Wiki encyclopedia software, known as MediaWiki, is carefully designed to allow easy reversal of editorial mistakes.

Because No More Heroes Wiki is an ongoing work to which in principle anybody can contribute, it differs from a paper-based reference source in some very important ways. In particular, older articles tend to be more comprehensive and balanced, while newer articles may still contain significant misinformation, unencyclopedic content, or vandalism. Users need to be aware of this in order to obtain valid information and avoid misinformation which has been recently added and not yet removed. However, unlike a paper reference source, No More Heroes Wiki can be constantly updated, with articles on topical events being created or updated within minutes or hours, rather than months or years for printed encyclopedias.

items.name: Death Note's Wiki
items.title: Death Note's Wiki
items.headline: Bienvenidos a Death Note Wiki
items.desc: Death Note (デスノートDesu Nōto) es una serie de manga escrita por Tsugumi Ōba e ilustrada por Takeshi Obata, y cuya adaptación al anime fue dirigida por Tetsurō Araki. La historia se centra en Light Yagami, un estudiante de preparatoria que encuentra un cuaderno sobrenatural llamado «Death Note», el cual es capaz de matar personas si se escriben los nombres de éstas en él mientras el portador visualiza mentalmente la cara de quien quiere asesinar. Light intenta eliminar a todos los criminales y crear un mundo donde no exista la maldad, pero sus planes serán frustrados por L, un famoso detective privado.

items.name: Super Mario Fanon
items.title: Super Mario Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to Mario Fanon Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to the Mario Fanon Wikia! The Mario Fanon Wikia is a Super Mario fanfiction wiki that anyone can edit. This site encourages fans of Mario to write anything, literally anything fictional, on Mario and his spin-offs, affiliates, friends, colleagues, villains, rooms, places, countries, leaders, species, etc.! Enter now to see what's on the site and how you can contribute!

items.name: Dragonball Fanon Wiki
items.title: Dragonball Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Dragon Ball Fanon Wiki
items.desc: Dragon Ball is one of the most popular mangas/animes of all time. With three story arcs, it has amassed a huge following of fans, many of whom enjoy the meta-series so much they create their own additions to Dragon Ball tale. These additions are known as fan fictions, or "fanons". Started in 2008, Dragon Ball Fanon Wiki is designed so that anyone can edit and add their own Dragon Ball, Dragon Ball Z, and/or Dragon Ball GT fan fiction and read other people's fan fictions. We accept almost all kinds of fan fiction, no matter what the content is, so long as it is inoffensive and appropriate for all ages.

items.name: Sonic Fanon Wiki
items.title: Sonic Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Sonic Fanon Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Sonic Fanon Wiki, an online community dedicated to the creations and ideas of all fans of the Sonic the Hedgehog franchise. Please help yourself by looking at and discussing other people's characters, creating own pages, joining roleplays, or just having a good time on our chat room.

items.name: South Park Fanon Wikia
items.title: South Park Fanon Wikia
items.headline: Welcome to the South Park Fanon Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to South Park Fanon Wikia! Here you can create and edit articles about your own characters, stories and additional things set in the same universe as the South Park television series. Just remember to read the rules and policies before creating any articles!

items.name: Higurashi no Naku Koro Ni Wiki
items.title: Higurashi no Naku Koro Ni Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Higurashi no Naku Koro ni Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Higurashi no Naku Koro ni Wiki!  We cover a large selection of Higurashi-related information, including characters, plot, music, anime, manga, video games and more. We are constantly growing, so feel free to jump in and join the community!

Thank you for stopping by, and happy reading!

items.name: LEGO Fanonpedia
items.title: LEGO Fanonpedia

items.desc: The LEGO Fanon Wiki is a community that aims to create the best resource for new LEGO Concepts! This Wiki is for users to show their ideas on what they thinks should be created from things related to the LEGO Group. Ideas such as sets, video games, themes, and more will be published into articles. Just like any wiki out there, anyone can edit!

items.name: Chrono Wiki
items.title: Chrono Wiki
items.headline: Chronopedia
items.desc: Chrono "Chronopedia" Wiki is dedicated to everything about The Chrono series, a video game franchise developed and published by Square Enix (formerly Square). It began in 1995 with the time travel console role-playing game Chrono Trigger, which spawned two continuations, Radical Dreamers and Chrono Cross.

items.name: Nodiatis Wiki
items.title: Nodiatis Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Nodiatis Wikia
items.desc: The Nodiatis Wikia is a community site dedicated to the browser-based game Nodiatis. If you are a fan of this game, or even if you're just curious about it, then this is the place for you! Come explore our content and help us expand this database... or join us in discussion about characters, quests, or the game in general. All are welcome!

items.name: Dinosaur King
items.title: Dinosaur King
items.headline: Dinosaur King Wiki
items.desc: Dinosaur King Wiki is all about Dinosaur King, an arcade game based on the Japanese beetle-fighting arcade game Mushiking, but uses dinosaurs instead of beetles. Eventually, it became a popular anime. With the popularity of the and the arcade game, SEGA and Upper Deck decided to build a trading card game around it, as well as a DS Game. To accompany the anime, a manga adaption has been made.

items.desc: The Wiki about R. Scott Bakker’s Second Apocalypse cycle that anyone can edit.

items.desc: Biblioteka Arkanii jest projektem fan-fiction dotyczącym serii "Gwiezdne Wojny". Jest to jeden z największych tego typu projektów na polskiej Wikii. Gwarantujemy miłą administrację, przyjemną atmosferę i przede wszystkim wspaniałą zabawę!

items.name: OnePiece Fanon Wiki
items.title: OnePiece Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the OnePiece Fanon Wiki
items.desc:
The One Piece Fanon Wiki began 29 July, 2008. Suggested by Yung Wun, the fanon was created with the intention of "sharing fun fan-made characters for others to critique in order to create realistic fanon One Piece characters."

Monkey D. Luffy refuses to let anyone or anything stand in the way of his quest to become the king of all pirates. With a course charted for the treacherous waters of the Grand Line and beyond, this is one captain who'll never give up until he's claimed the greatest treasure on Earth: the Legendary One Piece!

items.name: Power Rangers Fanon Wiki
items.title: Power Rangers Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Power Rangers Fanon!
items.desc: Power Rangers Fanon is the first wiki that lets you see the creations of other PR and Sentai fans as they create their own episodes, zords, megazords, series, etc. We have content from both Power Rangers and Super Sentai so start thinking and creating to make your own adventure in the PR/Sentai world!

items.name: Resident Evil Fanon Wiki
items.title: Resident Evil Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Gory Storm: Resident Evil Fanon Wiki
items.desc: We promote the healthy creativity of all Resident Evil fans. With our new "no follow plot" policy, any of those who were unhappy with their favorite game outcome, can change anything they wish, under the new admins. The wiki hopes to revive the undead spirit with the franchise. We are also hoping to get new members as our current member list is a bit short.

items.name: Bakugan Fanon Wiki
items.title: Bakugan Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Bakugan Fanon Wikia!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Bakugan Fanon wikia! The wikia is all about Bakugan fan fiction that anyone can edit. Our primary focus is fan fiction (aka fanon) so don't create already made characters, Bakugan, etc. — let your imagination run wild with new character ideas! We welcome new users and can't wait to see what creations you come up with.

Happy editing!

items.name: Medal of Honor Wiki
items.title: Medal of Honor Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Medal of Honor Wiki
items.desc:
This wikia is dedicated to one of the oldest FPSs out there, Medal of Honor. The forerunner to the Call of Duty series, Medal of Honor has an abundance of history that should be shared with avid gamers who respect such games. 
The newest game in the series is Medal of Honor: Warfighter, arriving on October 23rd. 
Editors are very welcome to come and help out with adding information to articles, adding images or other helpful things.

items.name: The Notion Club Archive
items.title: The Notion Club Archive
items.headline: Welcome to te Middle-earth Role Playing Wikia!
items.desc:
Welcome! The Middle-earth Role Playing Wiki is an encyclopedia dedicated to roleplaying games set in J.R.R. Tolkien´s Middle-earth. This Wiki will cover Expanded Middle-earth, the non-canonical subcreation made for Middle Earth Roleplaying (MERP), Questgame, Middle-Earth play-by-mail, Middle-Earth Collectible Card Game, Mithril Miniatures, as well as The Lord of the Rings Role-Playing Game, The One Ring - Roleplaying in Middle Earth, The Lord of the Rings Online and The Lord of the Rings Strategy Battle Game.

We welcome new users to join and edit the wikia with us!

items.name: Club Penguin Fan Universe
items.title: Club Penguin Fan Universe
items.headline: Welcome to the Club Penguin Fanon Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Club Penguin Fanon Wiki! Club Penguin is a massively multiplayer online game involving a virtual world containing a range of online games and activities, created by New Horizon Interactive. Players use cartoon penguin-avatars and play in a winter-set virtual world. 

This wiki is dedicated to all fanon related to Club Penguin. We welcome new users to come and edit on the wiki!

items.name: Wesnoth Wiki
items.title: Wesnoth Wiki
items.headline: Wesnoth Wiki-The Encyclopedia About The Battle For Wesnoth
items.desc: Wesnoth Wiki is a growing wiki about the strategy-war game, Battle for Wesnoth! With hacks, cheats, informational articles, Wesnoth Wiki is the best source for Wesnoth! We strive to have in-depth information on units and factions. Like the undead and elves. All help is greatly appreciated and we would love to see you around!

items.name: Super Smash Bros. Fanon
items.title: Super Smash Bros. Fanon
items.headline: Super Smash Bros. Fanon
items.desc: Super Smash Bros. Fanon is a wiki dedicated to the various fan-created Super Smash Bros. games, characters, stages and items! The wiki may contain some... more 'outrageous' ideas, but we accept any, and all, ideas! Actively monitored by the admins, the wiki also contains an online "magazine" entitled "The New Smash it Up", where some users write reviews on fan-games or talk about upcoming Nintendo games of interest.

items.name: How Not To Live Your Life Wiki
items.title: How Not To Live Your Life Wiki

items.name: Umineko no Naku Koro ni Wiki
items.title: Umineko no Naku Koro ni Wiki
items.headline: Collect the Umineko no Naku Koro ni Wiki!
items.desc:
The Wikia about the the anime, manga, and sound novel Umineko no Naku Koro ni.

Umineko no Naku Koro ni (うみねこのなく頃に, When the Seagulls Cry) is a Japanese murder mystery dōjin soft visual novel series produced by 07th Expansion (Ryukishi07).

The word "umineko" is the name of a kind of seagull known as a Black-tailed Gull. Naku means "to cry" or "to make a sound" (鳴く), referring only to sounds made by non-humans when written with that kanji; no kanji is provided in the series logo, however. According to Ryukishi07, the red Na (な) in the logo is an official part of the title.

The Umineko no Naku Koro ni games are the first four games in the series which are meant to give the player a sense of the world where the story takes place and introduce the mysterious circumstances surrounding Rokkenjima and the legend of the Golden Witch. Each arc in this series contains all the previous arcs.

items.name: La Wikia de Pokéfanon
items.title: La Wikia de Pokéfanon

items.desc: Si jugando a Pokémon alguna vez has experimentado la sensación de vivir más aventuras, tus propias aventuras, has dado con el lugar correcto. Aquí podrás crear tus propias historias sobre Pokémon apartándote tanto como necesites de las líneas originales

items.name: Pikcanon-NOT
items.title: Pikcanon-NOT
items.headline: Welcome to the Pikmin Fanon Wikia!
items.desc: The Pikmin Fanon Wikia is the place to write and read Pikmin fanon. Create your own tales, based on the games or on your original idea! The Pikcanon-NOT Constitution is the agreed upon rules list for all users. They are voted for in polls and then are added by an admin to the "New Orders" section. All changes to already existing rules are to be marked in Italics and all removed rules will be crossed out.

items.name: Luminous Arc Wiki
items.title: Luminous Arc Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Luminous Arc wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Luminous Arc Wiki! We are crafting the ultimate reference guide to the Luminous Arc series, and because it is a wiki you can help! The game was produced by the video game development companies Marvelous Interactive Inc. and Image Epoch for the Nintendo DS hand-held game system, a product of Nintendo. Luminous Arc was released in Japan on February 8, 2007 by Marvelous Interactive Inc. and August 14, 2007 in North America by ATLUS. The game was released in Europe on October 12, 2007 by Rising Star Games.

items.name: Fallout Fanon Wiki
items.title: Fallout Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Scour the Tranquility Lane Wiki!
items.desc:
Tranquility Lane is the Fallout Fanon Wiki - a community where you can create your own stories, characters and places in the universe of the Fallout series of games, using the latest Vault-Tec simulation technology. (Tranquility Lane is not an RP (roleplaying) wiki.)

Expanding the Fallout Universe since 2077!

items.name: Anime Fanon
items.title: Anime Fanon
items.headline: Explore the Anime Fanon Wikia
items.desc: The Anime Fanon Wikia community was developed by users who like to write fan fiction specifically related to anime. On this roleplaying community, users are free to write their own stories and tales as long as they are based in an anime setting. We are always looking for new contributors and would be delighted to enjoy your stories.

items.name: Mega Man Fanon Wiki
items.title: Mega Man Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Mega Man Fanon Wiki!
items.desc:
The wiki that aims to be the home of Mega Man Fanon and fanstuff. We are always accepting submissions! We are a community that aims to create the best resource for the Mega Man Fanon series, a series of action games developed by Capcom. 

Mega Man is a video game franchise from Capcom, starring the robot character Mega Man, or one of his many counterparts. Mega Man, released for the Nintendo Entertainment System in 1987, began a series of over 50 games on multiple systems. As of December 31, 2010, the series has sold approximately twenty-nine million copies worldwide, making it Capcom's most prolific franchise.

items.name: Shakugan no Shana Wiki
items.title: Shakugan no Shana Wiki
items.headline: Shakugan no Shana Wiki
items.desc: Shakugan no Shana Wiki is a  free online resource for the Shakugan no Shana franchise. Originally a light novel series created by Yashichiro Takahashi, the franchise had been adapted into a manga and a trilogy of anime series. The story focuses on Yuji Sakai, a high school boy who inadvertently becomes involved in an age-old conflict between forces of balance and imbalance in existence. In the process, he befriends a fighter for the balancing force and names her "Shana". The series incorporates fantasy and slice of life elements into its tale.

items.name: Monster Hunter Fanon
items.title: Monster Hunter Fanon
items.headline: Join the Monster Hunter Fanon Wiki
items.desc: The Monster Hunter Fanon Wiki is a comprehensive database made by fans of the Monster Hunter Series. This Wiki will contain anything made by fans (from Fan-Art, to Fan-Fiction, to crossovers, and even their very own Cosplay Pictures). A Fan-Fiction can be novels, short stories, poems, etc. Users can also create their very own clan and recruit their own clan members.
